Event_Description: The GURR site has a sandy sediment bottom amongst large boulders. It is located in a Special Area of Conservation. A video of the first deployment in July 2020 which shows details of the site can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sckV0FIAXd8. The excel sheets uploaded as "Associated Data" contain 1) the index to the photo labels and 2) manual observations (in fact, none were made). A single image "subsampled" shows tunicate biomass removed from GURR3 prior to metabarcoding (so as not to drown out the signal from smaller organisms - a small amount of these tunicates were nevertheless included for barcoding).

The GURR site has a sandy sediment bottom amongst large boulders. It is located in a Special Area of Conservation. A video of this site (taken at a previous visit in July 2020) shows details of the site. This can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sckV0FIAXd8.  

Associated files which have been uploaded for this sampling event show photos of all plates at Gurr 2 for the Summer 2021- Summer 2022 deployment. Photo image files are labelled by deployment dates and plate number. Plate numbers and deployment date labels are also clearly visible in the photographs.
